

=Bio=

"In 1987 he was a founding vice-president of the Society for the History of Mediaeval Technology and Science, the British affiliate of AVISTA and the Association de Villard de Honnecourt.
Gimpel, a lifelong Communist, believed that the basis of sustainable development in the developing world should be low-tech mediaeval machines that could be built, maintained, repaired and replaced using local craftsmen and resources. He was a founder of Models for Rural Development, part of the Appropriate Technology movement."
(https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jean_Gimpel)

